WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-US

00:00:25.192 --> 00:00:28.552
The single of Overkill was released on 16th February 1979

00:00:28.552 --> 00:00:31.022
and reached #39 on the UK singles chart.

00:00:54.741 --> 00:00:57.991
Overkill the album was recorded at Roundhouse Studios

00:00:57.991 --> 00:01:00.891
by former Rolling Stones producer, Jimmy Miller.

00:01:24.737 --> 00:01:27.527
It was the first time Phil ‘Philthy Animal’ Taylor

00:01:27.527 --> 00:01:29.437
played double bass on a song

00:01:29.437 --> 00:01:32.987
and was often played as an extended version live as the finale.

00:01:55.212 --> 00:01:57.982
The cover of both the Overkill single and album

00:01:57.982 --> 00:02:00.142
were created by artist Joe Petagno.

00:02:29.728 --> 00:02:33.728
Overkill charted at #24 on the UK album chart, their highest to date.

00:02:56.425 --> 00:02:59.475
They also performed the song on Top Of The Pops.

00:03:25.179 --> 00:03:29.809
The song has been covered by Metallica, Overkill and Grave Digger over the years.

00:03:56.787 --> 00:03:59.797
Overkill featured on the video games SSX On Tour

00:03:59.797 --> 00:04:01.597
and Guitar Hero World Tour

00:04:01.597 --> 00:04:04.487
where you could play along to the song on guitar

00:04:25.177 --> 00:04:28.177
Overkill closed the bands live set on their final tour,

00:04:28.177 --> 00:04:31.377
meaning it was the last song they ever played together.

